Rename the `tokio` crate to `pausable-tokio` and detach it from the
workspace for publishing.

This patch is intended to be the LAST patch applied, immediately before
`cargo publish`. Apply order is:

    0001-pausable-time-runtime.patch   (source code changes)
    0002-pausable-time-deps.patch      (Cargo.toml: pausable_clock dep)
    0003-pausable-time-tests.patch     (integration tests)
    0004-rename-for-crates-io.patch    (this patch: crate name + detach)

Keeping the rename in its own patch lets you build, test, and run the
modified code under the original `tokio` name during development -- which
matters because tokio's own internal tests reference `tokio::...` paths
that would otherwise need rewriting.

Four hunks together:

  * `tokio/Cargo.toml` -- prepend an empty `[workspace]` section so cargo
    treats this crate as its own workspace root. Decoupling it from the
    parent workspace is required because the parent's other members
    (`benches`, `tokio-util`, etc.) still path-depend on a crate named
    literally `tokio` and break the moment we rename.
  * `tokio/Cargo.toml` -- rename `name = "tokio"` to `name = "pausable-tokio"`.
  * `tokio/Cargo.toml` -- drop the trailing `[lints] workspace = true`
    block. Now that the crate is its own workspace root, that line
    would cause `cargo` to look for a `[workspace.lints]` section in
    *this* `Cargo.toml`, which doesn't exist. The lints aren't
    important for the published artifact, so we just remove the block.
  * Workspace `Cargo.toml` -- drop the `tokio` entry from `members` and
    drop the `[patch.crates-io] tokio = { path = "tokio" }` line. The
    other workspace members (benches, tokio-util, etc.) will pick up
    `tokio` from crates.io if they're built after this patch. We leave
    them in the workspace because the user might still want to e.g.
    `cargo build -p tokio-util` after the rename.

The cumulative effect: `cd tokio && cargo publish` works regardless of
prior cargo state in the parent workspace; the rest of the workspace
remains buildable in the post-rename state (it just uses upstream
`tokio` instead of the local one).
diff --git a/Cargo.toml b/Cargo.toml
--- a/Cargo.toml
+++ b/Cargo.toml
@@ -1,7 +1,6 @@
 [workspace]
 resolver = "2"
 members = [
-  "tokio",
   "tokio-macros",
   "tokio-test",
   "tokio-stream",
@@ -16,7 +15,6 @@ members = [
 ]
 
 [patch.crates-io]
-tokio = { path = "tokio" }
 tokio-macros = { path = "tokio-macros" }
 tokio-stream = { path = "tokio-stream" }
 tokio-test = { path = "tokio-test" }
diff --git a/tokio/Cargo.toml b/tokio/Cargo.toml
--- a/tokio/Cargo.toml
+++ b/tokio/Cargo.toml
@@ -1,5 +1,9 @@
+[workspace]
+# Detach this crate from the parent workspace so it can be published
+# standalone as `pausable-tokio`.
+
 [package]
-name = "tokio"
+name = "pausable-tokio"
 # When releasing to crates.io:
 # - Remove path dependencies (if any)
 # - Update doc url
@@ -191,5 +195,3 @@ allowed_external_types = [
   "tokio_macros::*",
 ]
 
-[lints]
-workspace = true
